  <p align="right"><strong>Resolution Number: </strong><!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="Resolution Number" --><strong>A041</strong><!-- InstanceEndEditable -->&nbsp;</p>
  <h1>Subject: <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="Resolution Name" -->The Constitution - Voting in the Council of General Synod<!-- InstanceEndEditable --></h1>
  <p>Moved by:&nbsp;<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="moved-by" -->Ronald Stevenson (Chancellor)<!-- InstanceEndEditable --></p>
  <p>Seconded By:&nbsp;<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="seconded-by" -->Robert Falby from the Diocese of Toronto<!-- InstanceEndEditable --></p>
  <p><strong>Note: The mover and the seconder must be members of the General Synod and be present in the House when the resolution is before the synod for debate.</strong></p>
  <p><strong>BE IT RESOLVED:</strong></p>
  <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="Motion" -->
  <p>That section 35 of the Constitution of the General Synod be amended by re-lettering paragraph e) to be paragraph f) and adding the following new paragraph e):</p>
  <blockquote>
    <p>e) All motions in the Council of the General Synod shall be decided by the votes of all of the members of the Council taken collectively.</p>
  </blockquote>
  <!-- InstanceEndEditable -->
  <p><strong>EXPLANATORY NOTE/BACKGROUND INFORMATION:</strong></p>
  <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="note" -->The purpose of the amendment is to clarify that there is no voting by Orders in the Council of the General Synod.<!-- InstanceEndEditable -->
  <p align="right">Source: <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="source" -->The Council of the General Synod <!-- InstanceEndEditable --><br />
  (name of committee, diocese, etc.)</p>
  <p align="right">Submitted by: <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="sub-by" -->The General Secretary<!-- InstanceEndEditable --></p>
  <p>A)	Does this motion contain within it any financial implications? </p>
  <p>Yes ___<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="fy" -->_<!-- InstanceEndEditable -->__   No ___<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="fn" -->_<!-- InstanceEndEditable -->__</p>
  <p>B)	If yes, has the General Synod Expenditures Committee considered the implications?</p>
  <p>Yes ___<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="ey" -->_<!-- InstanceEndEditable -->__   No ___<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="en" -->_<!-- InstanceEndEditable -->__</p>
